Rand Merchant Bank has released the eighth edition of its Where to invest in Africa report, which analyses 53 African economies according to their investment attractiveness. The theme of this year’s report is infrastructure, one of the most important aspects of doing business on the continent. In this video Celeste Fauconnier, Africa analyst at RMB, gives insight into the business environments of these countries based on the report’s findings. Brought to you by Rand Merchant Bank (RMB).